  "local_port": 54888,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What can substitute butter in a brownies recipe?",
  "response": "There are several substitutes you can use for butter in a brownie recipe, depending on your dietary needs and what you have on hand. Here are some common alternatives:\n\n1. **Vegetable Oil**: This is one of the easiest and most common substitutes for butter in baking. Use the same amount of oil as the amount of butter called for in the recipe. For example, if the recipe calls for 1 cup of butter, use 1 cup of vegetable oil. \n\n2. **Coconut Oil**: This is another good substitute, and it can add a subtle coconut flavor to your brownies. Use it in a 1:1 ratio, just like vegetable oil.\n\n3. **Greek Yogurt**: If you want to keep the brownies moist but add a bit of tanginess, Greek yogurt can be a good choice. Use half the amount of yogurt as the butter called for in the recipe. For example, if the recipe calls for 1 cup of butter, use \u00bd cup of Greek yogurt.\n\n4. **Applesauce**: This is a great option if you want to reduce the fat content of your brownies. Use the same amount of applesauce as the butter called for in the recipe. Keep in mind that applesauce will add some sweetness and moisture to the brownies.\n\n5. **Avocado**: Mashed avocado can replace butter in a 1:1 ratio and will add healthy fats and a creamy texture to your brownies. The flavor of avocado is quite mild, so it won\u2019t overpower the chocolate.\n\n6. **Margarine**: If you're looking for a direct substitute, margarine can work well in a 1:1 ratio with butter. However, choose a margarine that is meant for baking to ensure the best results.\n\n7. **Nut Butters**: Almond butter, peanut butter, or other nut butters can add a unique flavor to your brownies. Use them in a 1:1 ratio with butter, but keep in mind that they will impart a nutty taste to your brownies.\n\nWhen substituting butter, keep in mind that each alternative may slightly change the texture and flavor of your brownies. You might need to experiment a bit to find the perfect substitute for your recipe.",
